        <para>
            If you click on the first button at the top 
            &#160;<graphic fileref="../themes/default/images/arrow_out.png" align="center" valign="middle"/>&#160;, 
            all folders are opened, whereas all folders close if you click the second button
            &#160;<graphic fileref="../themes/default/images/arrow_in.png" align="center" valign="middle"/>&#160;. 
            The third button
            &#160;<graphic fileref="../themes/default/images/arrow_refresh.png" align="center" valign="middle"/>&#160; 
            for reloading the folder view is only needed if you work in the database for a long time and new folders 
            have been created (or deleted) by others since you logged in.
        </para>
        <note>
            <para>Known Bug:</para>
            <para>When you perform a search in a folder, the other folders contained in this folder disappear.</para>
            <para>Workaround: Close down all folders by clicking the second button, 
                then update by clicking the third button, then access the same level in the folder hierarchy again.</para>
        </note>
